</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="118" pageNumber="119" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
Annual herb, commonly branched at the base, reaching c. 40 cm, stems and leaves with long, stiff spreading hairs. Basal leaves 2.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.7-1 cm, obovate-spathulate, obtuse, entire, base attenuate into a pseudopetiole, stem leaves 1.5-5.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-1(-1.8) cm, oblong or lanceolate, sessile. Flowers solitary, axillary, pedunculate; bracts lanceolate, acute; peduncles 1.5-5 cm, slender, flexuose, becoming recurved in fruit; bracteoles 0.5 mm, triangular, acute; pedicels 2-4 mm, not well differentiated from the peduncles; sepals 5-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-2.5 mm, ovate, acute to apiculate, margin, scarious, ciliate or glabrous, sepals otherwise more or less glabrous; corolla 1.5-2.4 cm long, tricoloured blue, white and yellow, weakly 5-angled with apices of lobes pointed, midpetaline bands adpressed pilose; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided c. 5 mm above base, stigmas 2.5-3 mm. Capsule glabrous, much exceeding calyx; seeds tuberculate. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 185; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pignatti, S" journalOrPublisher="Edagricole, Bologna" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="386 - 390" refId="B269" refString="Pignatti, S, 1982. Flora D'Italia. Edagricole, Bologna: 386 - 390" title="Flora D'Italia" year="1982">Pignatti 1982</bibRefCitation>
: 388; 
<bibRefCitation author="Silvestre, S" editor="Talevera, S" journalOrPublisher="Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid" pageId="211" pageNumber="212" pagination="252 - 273" refId="B337" refString="Silvestre, S, 2012. Convolvulus. In: Talevera, S, Andres, C, Arista, M, Fernandes Piedra, MP, Gallego, MJ, Ortiz, PL, Romero Zarco, C, Salgueiro, FJ, Silvestre, S, Quinanar, A, Eds., Flora Iberica volume 11: Gentianaceae to Boraginaceae. Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid: 252 - 273" title="Convolvulus." volumeTitle="Flora Iberica volume 11: Gentianaceae to Boraginaceae." year="2012">Silvestre 2012</bibRefCitation>
: 268, 271 (plate)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="118" pageNumber="119" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
West Mediterranean region, perhaps only in Europe: Algeria (?); Morocco (?); Portugal (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Brummitt &amp; Ernst</emphasis>
5985); Spain (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Boissier &amp; Reuter</emphasis>
1841, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Todaro</emphasis>
922); Italy (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Woolley-Dod</emphasis>
1756).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="118" pageNumber="119" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
Somewhat resembling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Syst. Nat. ed. 12, 3: 229. 1768. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1768" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus pentapetaloides" order="Solanales" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pentapetaloides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Convolvulus pentapetaloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but corolla much larger.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
